        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/30794",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Please be patient:\nOnly because I began to add locale awareness to some filters it does not mean that these validators don't work.\n\nEach addition has to go through a review process and this takes time.\n\nAccording to \"number validator inside Abstract class\"...\nDefinetly no: Abstract should not add validator specific rules or methods.\n\nA validator for StringLength or a Regex validator don't have the need to use localizing methods.\n\nAnd float and boolean have different needs of localization.\nThis won't work.\n\nValidators have eighter to be independent from each other, OR the extend each other. So when a Between validator needs number validation it should extend Zend_Validate_Number or a related validator.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-05-09T02:28:30.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-05-09T02:28:30.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/32219",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "@dev-team:\nThe following validators need localization to have a unique API:\n* Zend_Validate_Between\n* Zend_Validate_GreaterThan\n* Zend_Validate_LessThan\n\nThe proposed way is to have each validator independently from others even if this would mean to duplicate existing code. The API of all 5 validators (Int and Float are already localized) should be completly the same.\n\nThe API itself is\n* setLocale\n* getLocale\n* Setting the locale at initiation\n* No locale set -> use non-localized behaviour",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-06-26T12:11:28.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-06-26T12:11:28.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
